*********
Snapshots
*********

> Connect to the EC2 instance

> Volume

> Select the HDD which wants to take snapshot

> Actions

> Create Snapshot

> Now, Backup is created

***Go To Terminal for Backup & Disaster Recovery***

> Connect to the EC2 instance

> Snapshot

> Select the Snapshot which wants to take Backup & Disaster Recovery

> Actions

> Select- Create volume from snapshot

> Volume




Check whether volume is attached
# lsblk

> Chek if there is any data on volume
# file -s /dev/xvdf

> Create a file system for volume
# mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf

# mkdir /fileserver
 
# mount /dev/xvdf /fileserver

# cd /fileserver

# ls

# lost+found (This is confimation for it is fresh format disc)

> Remove lost+found 
# sudo rm -rf

> Create some files using nano

> Unmount the volume 
# umount /dev/xvdf

> Check whether volume is unmounted or not
# cd /fileserver
# ls
